title: Unemployment rate in Lithuania 2019
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, containing a total of 21 data points.
Overall Unemployment rate has decreased over the Year.
The line significantly increased by 7.96 from Year 2008 to 2009.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2008 and 2009.
Maximum Unemployment rate, about 17.81 was reported at Year 2010
Minimum Unemployment rate about 4.25 was reached at Year 2007
min_summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, containing a total of 21 data points.
Overall Unemployment rate has decreased over the Year.

Unemployment rate is roughly constant from 1999 to 2003, slightly decreasing from 2003 to 2006, rapidly increasing from 2006 to 2010, roughly constant from 2010 to 2014, roughly decreasing from 2014 to 2015, and lastly roughly constant from 2015 to 2019.
